A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Tax
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The percentage of money requested by the government for this specified product or transaction.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Tax indicates the type of tax for this document line.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Tax Search Key
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A fast method for finding a specific tax.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Tax Indicator identifies the short name that will print on documents referencing this tax.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Valid From Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A parameter stating the starting time of a specified request.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Valid From date indicates the first day of a date range

AD_FIELD.NAME: Summary Level
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A means of grouping fields in order to view or hide additional information.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A summary entity represents a branch in a tree rather than an end-node. Summary entities are used for reporting and do not have own values.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Rate
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The percentage to be multiplied by the source to arrive at the tax or exchange amount.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Rate indicates the percentage to be multiplied by the source to arrive at the tax or exchange amount.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Parent Tax Rate
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Parent Tax indicates a tax that is made up of multiple taxes
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Parent Tax indicates a tax that is a reference for multiple taxes. This allows you to charge multiple taxes on a document by entering the Parent Tax

AD_FIELD.NAME: Country
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A state or a nation.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Country defines a Country. Each Country must be defined before it can be used in any document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Region
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An area of a specific country.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Region identifies a unique Region for this Country.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Destination Country
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The country receiving a shipment
AD_FIELD.HELP: The To Country indicates the receiving country on a document

AD_FIELD.NAME: Destination Region
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The state/province inside of a country receiving the shipment.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The To Region indicates the receiving region on a document

AD_FIELD.NAME: Tax Exempt
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A condition stating that for a specific case, taxes must not be applied.
AD_FIELD.HELP: If a business partner is exempt from tax, the exempt tax rate is used. For this, you need to set up a tax rate with a 0% rate and indicate that this is your tax exempt rate. This is required for tax reporting, so that you can track tax exempt transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Sales/Purchase Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Sales Tax applies to sales situations, Purchase Tax to purchase situations
AD_FIELD.HELP: Sales Tax: charged when selling - examples: Sales Tax, Output VAT (payable)Purchase Tax: tax charged when purchasing - examples: Use Tax, Input VAT (receivable)

AD_FIELD.NAME: Line No.
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A line stating the position of this request in the document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the unique line for a document. It will also control the display order of the lines within a document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Cascade
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Any additional discount built upon the remaining total after applying previous discounts.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates if it is applied in an accumulative way or if it is applied to the base amount.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Tax Category
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A classification of tax options based on similar characteristics or attributes.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Tax Category provides a method of grouping similar taxes. For example, Sales Tax or Value Added Tax.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Business Partner Tax Category
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Bussines Partner Tax Category as a Vendor
AD_FIELD.HELP: Bussines Partner Tax Category is a category defined for applying default taxes to procurement transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Import Taxes
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Import Taxes
AD_FIELD.HELP: Import Taxes from temporary tables to real ones.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Processed
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A confirmation that the associated documents or requests are processed.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Processed checkbox indicates that a document has been processed.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Import Error Message
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A message that appears when errors occur during the importing process.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Import Error Message displays any error messages generated during the import process.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Import Process Complete
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A indication that the desired process has been completed successfully.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Imported check box indicates if this import has been processed.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Creation Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The date that this record is completed.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Created field indicates the date that this record was created.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Element Level
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Element Level
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the level of the account (heading, account, breakdown or subaccount).

AD_FIELD.NAME: Account Element
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A identification code for an account type.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Account Elements can be natural accounts or user defined values.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Accounting Schema
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The structure used in accounting including costing methods, currencies, and the calendar.
AD_FIELD.HELP: An Accounting Schema defines the rules used in accounting such as costing method, currency and calendar

AD_FIELD.NAME: Attribute Set Value
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An attribute associated with a product as part of an attribute set.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The values of the actual Product Attributes

AD_FIELD.NAME: Attributeset Identification
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The identifier for the attribute set. This identifier is the result of all the columns that are marked as isidentifier
